IIRC, the [OpenIDConnect spec allows](https://openid.net/specs/openid-connect-core-1_0.html#Authentication) specifying multiple, space-separated response types.

Should this line be something like:

`if not set(request.response_type.split()).issubset(self.response_types):`

text: This feels a bit hacky. If I understand correctly, in this scenario, we've already generated an access token, but then we're just throwing it away and not returning it to the user? I guess that's fine, but it seems like we should be able to do better and avoid creating access tokens we don't need. Can we dispatch on response_type earlier in the flow somewhere?
